00:19:04,826 --> 00:19:06,827
If he'd stayed on the plane,
he'd be dead.

248
00:19:08,997 --> 00:19:12,750
If everybody thinks he's dead, he
won't have to pay the 15 or the vig.

249
00:19:12,917 --> 00:19:15,044
Keep going.

250
00:19:15,211 --> 00:19:18,714
Leo's wife is brought to the airport

251
00:19:18,882 --> 00:19:21,800
to get any personal effects
that weren't destroyed.

252
00:19:21,968 --> 00:19:26,388
Leo's bags were on the plane,
so the wife tells 'em what to look for.

253
00:19:26,556 --> 00:19:28,390
(gasps) Ah!

254
00:19:29,434 --> 00:19:31,644
(sobs)

255
00:19:35,148 --> 00:19:39,652
Oh, my Leo! My Leo!

256
00:19:39,819 --> 00:19:42,363
Later, the airline people
visit his wife...

257
00:19:42,530 --> 00:19:46,450
...and offer her a settlement,

258
00:19:46,618 --> 00:19:50,496
based on what he would've earned from
the dry-cleaner's the rest of his life.

259
00:19:50,664 --> 00:19:55,918
- So how much is that?
- 300 grand. So they take it.

260
00:19:56,086 --> 00:19:59,963
He gets his wife to cash the check
and he goes to Vegas with the dough.

261
00:20:00,131 --> 00:20:03,467
He should call her
to let her know when to come.

262
00:20:03,635 --> 00:20:08,263
She never hears from him, but
he turns the 300,000 into 500,000.

263
00:20:09,766 --> 00:20:13,102
But he's winning
and he can't tell anyone who he is!

264
00:20:13,269 --> 00:20:17,272
So we're showing his desire
to be famous.

265
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,358
He's got the dough
to buy his way in,

266
00:20:19,526 --> 00:20:23,779
mix with the celebs,
and he can't resist, so he comes to LA.

267
00:20:23,947 --> 00:20:28,242
I dunno about the celebrities.
That was just added,

268
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:32,871
but, yeah, he comes to LA and...
I don't know what happens next.

269
00:20:33,456 --> 00:20:35,457
That's it, that's your movie?

270
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:37,459
I said I had an idea for a movie.

271
00:20:37,627 --> 00:20:40,129
That's half a movie with holes in it.

272
00:20:40,296 --> 00:20:42,214
There's maybe 40 minutes there.

273
00:20:42,382 --> 00:20:47,386
You don't have a girl, a female lead,
or anybody to sympathize with.

274
00:20:47,554 --> 00:20:49,972
- You don't have a good guy.
- The shylock is a good guy.

275
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:52,141
(Harry) The shylock is barely mentioned.

276
00:20:52,308 --> 00:20:55,018
And it's not believable the wife'd
get a settlement that fast.

277
00:20:55,186 --> 00:20:58,897
Harry doesn't realize it's
a true story. That Miami flight?

278
00:20:59,065 --> 00:21:02,151
On the news every day for a week.
Harry must have been busy.

279
00:21:02,318 --> 00:21:05,154
- That's where you got the idea?
- Part of it, yeah.

280
00:21:06,156 --> 00:21:08,741
You're not the guy, the dry-cleaner?

281
00:21:08,908 --> 00:21:11,827
- Leo.
- No, you wouldn't be talking to me.

282
00:21:11,995 --> 00:21:15,038
- No, I'm not the guy, Harry.
- But you do work for the casino?

283
00:21:15,206 --> 00:21:17,750
For God's sake, he's the shylock.

284
00:21:17,917 --> 00:21:20,169
That's what you do?

285
00:21:20,336 --> 00:21:22,504
That's what I did.

286
00:21:22,672 --> 00:21:25,466
After I'm done here,
I don't know what I'll do.

287
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:27,634
Well, I got an early call.

288
00:21:27,802 --> 00:21:30,429
No problemo. Go on up to bed.

289
00:21:30,597 --> 00:21:35,809
Harry, I would like you and your
new buddy to get out of my house.

290
00:21:35,977 --> 00:21:37,936
Oh, yeah. Well, sure.

291
00:21:38,104 --> 00:21:41,648
It was absolutely a pleasure
to meet you, Karen.

292
00:21:43,193 --> 00:21:44,359
Hmm.

293
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:57,498
I guess there's times
you have to get rough,

294
00:21:57,665 --> 00:22:00,167
if one of your customers don't pay.

295
00:22:00,335 --> 00:22:01,710
They always pay.

296
00:22:02,921 --> 00:22:04,213
You pack a gun?

297
00:22:05,131 --> 00:22:06,215
Not really.

298
00:22:06,382 --> 00:22:07,883
Ever been arrested?

299
00:22:08,051 --> 00:22:13,055
I've been picked up for loan sharking
and racketeering, but never convicted.

300
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:18,685
Racketeering.
Covers a lot of ground, doesn't it?

301
00:22:18,853 --> 00:22:21,939
Get to the point, Harry. You want me
to do something for you?

302
00:22:34,244 --> 00:22:35,452
That's us.

303
00:23:28,423 --> 00:23:30,674
Good girl. Good girl.

304
00:23:33,177 --> 00:23:36,889
Don't say nothin', just sit
and act like you're waiting.

305
00:23:37,056 --> 00:23:39,892
What you talkin' about?
Give me the fuckin' money.

306
00:23:40,059 --> 00:23:41,351
Sit down.

307
00:23:43,271 --> 00:23:47,816
Now be lookin'.
Man to your right in the blue shirt.

308
00:23:47,984 --> 00:23:50,569
The other way. Derecho.

309
00:23:50,737 --> 00:23:52,988
That's a federal officer.

310
00:23:53,156 --> 00:23:57,075
Most likely DEA.
He moves his leg, look for the bulge.

311
00:23:57,243 --> 00:23:58,535
Savvy "bulge"?

312
00:23:58,703 --> 00:24:01,663
That's his backup piece.

313
00:24:01,831 --> 00:24:04,750
Try it without lookin' right at him.

314
00:24:05,585 --> 00:24:07,669
- What's your name?
- Yayo Portillo.

315
00:24:07,837 --> 00:24:13,091
All right, I'm gonna get up,
when I'm gone you sit in this seat,

316
00:24:13,259 --> 00:24:17,012
under you ass is a key to a locker
where your half million is,

317
00:24:17,180 --> 00:24:19,348
along with some product
we're returning.

318
00:24:19,515 --> 00:24:21,975
Powder's been stepped on
so many times it's baby food.

319
00:24:22,143 --> 00:24:23,644
You're supposed to give me
the money yourself!

320
00:24:23,811 --> 00:24:25,520
Try to be cool, yahoo.

321
00:24:27,774 --> 00:24:32,527
I told you where it is. Do it how
I told you, and have a safe trip home.

322
00:24:50,546 --> 00:24:54,257
What'd you have for breakfast, baby?
How come you weigh so much?

323
00:24:55,176 --> 00:24:56,677
You have a burrito?

324
00:24:57,553 --> 00:25:00,889
OK, give it to the nice lady,
there you go.

325
00:25:04,852 --> 00:25:06,311
- Say thank you.
- Thank you.

326
00:25:06,479 --> 00:25:07,729
Bye-bye.

327
00:25:11,025 --> 00:25:13,068
Like fucking clockwork, huh, Bear?

328
00:25:13,236 --> 00:25:16,738
- Hi, Bo.
- Ready to go for a ride, sweetie?

329
00:25:16,906 --> 00:25:19,199
I told you to watch your mouth
round my daughter.

330
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:24,037
(announcer)
The white zone is for loading only.

331
00:25:25,665 --> 00:25:28,917
These guys, my investors,
they run a limo service,

332
00:25:29,085 --> 00:25:33,922
..put money in some of my pictures,
did OK, they're happy.

333
00:25:34,674 --> 00:25:38,135
This was a few months ago,
when I was planning my next picture,

334
00:25:38,302 --> 00:25:42,764
about this band of killer circus freaks.

335
00:25:42,932 --> 00:25:47,060
There's this 700lb fat lady,
has a way of seducing guys,

336
00:25:47,228 --> 00:25:49,271
Harry, look at me.

337
00:25:49,439 --> 00:25:52,107
You're trying to tell me you fucked up
without sounding stupid.

338
00:25:52,275 --> 00:25:55,444
That's hard to do.
Let's talk about where you're at, OK?

339
00:25:55,611 --> 00:26:01,533
You blew 200 grand of their money
in Vegas and didn't tell 'em. Why?

340
00:26:01,701 --> 00:26:05,454
They wouldn't have taken it
with any understanding or restraint.

341
00:26:07,290 --> 00:26:10,709
If you're so scared,
why take it to Vegas to begin with?

342
00:26:10,877 --> 00:26:12,961
I needed half a million to buy a script.

343
00:26:15,131 --> 00:26:16,840
A blockbuster, but quality.

344
00:26:17,008 --> 00:26:20,302
No mutants or maniacs.
This is gonna be my Driving Miss Daisy.

345
00:26:24,307 --> 00:26:30,312
Murray Saffron, who wrote my Grotesque
pictures, showed it to me one day,

346
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:33,273
said he's got a star interested,
would I produce?

347
00:26:33,441 --> 00:26:34,524
Which star?

348
00:26:34,692 --> 00:26:37,694
Two-time Academy Award nominee,
Martin Weir.

349
00:26:39,655 --> 00:26:43,992
That's Martin Weir!
He played the mob guy in Cyclone.

350
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,368
One of his best parts.

351
00:26:45,536 --> 00:26:48,580
No, his best part was the crippled
gay guy who climbed Mt. Whitney.

352
00:26:48,748 --> 00:26:50,290
(Harry) Ride The Clouds.

353
00:26:50,458 --> 00:26:52,626
The woman, she looks familiar.

354
00:26:52,794 --> 00:26:56,671
She's a rock star.
Every day they have breakfast.

355
00:26:56,839 --> 00:27:01,802
He faces west, so he sees his billboard.
She faces east so she can wear shades.

356
00:27:02,845 --> 00:27:07,474
Anyway, Murray's shrink is
Martin's personal trainer's shrink.

357
00:27:07,642 --> 00:27:11,353
Murray's shrink gives
the script to Martin's trainer,

358
00:27:11,521 --> 00:27:13,522
who reads it to Martin.

359
00:27:13,689 --> 00:27:15,398
Martin loves it.

360
00:27:15,566 --> 00:27:19,528
- So what's the problem?
- Problem is Murray. Heart attack.

361
00:27:19,695 --> 00:27:23,573
Doris, Murray's widow,
hears about the Martin Weir thing,

362
00:27:23,741 --> 00:27:27,536
and because we didn't have a contract,
she wants half a million for the script.

363
00:27:27,703 --> 00:27:32,165
Ah, so you want my dry-cleaner
to invest in your movie.

364
00:27:32,333 --> 00:27:36,378
That, or what if some accident
was to befall the widow Saffron?

365
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:39,965
No, I'm not gonna pop her, OK?

366
00:27:40,133 --> 00:27:41,466
It was just a thought.

367
00:27:43,469 --> 00:27:46,221
I'll meet these limo guys,
tell 'em to leave you alone

368
00:27:46,389 --> 00:27:48,223
in a way they'll understand.

369
00:27:48,391 --> 00:27:49,891
You don't know these guys.

370
00:27:50,059 --> 00:27:52,811
Believe me, I know 'em
a whole lot better than you do.

371
00:28:10,872 --> 00:28:15,584
I asked this literary agent what kind of
writing paid best, he said ransom notes.

372
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,463
Here it is, Mr. Lovejoy.

373
00:28:27,263 --> 00:28:31,183
"Lovejoy sits at the wheel,
watching the bar across the street..."

374
00:28:31,350 --> 00:28:33,727
- Is he following someone?
- Read it, it's a grabber.

375
00:28:42,653 --> 00:28:45,447
Harry, I think your investors are here.

376
00:28:45,615 --> 00:28:46,823
Oh, Jesus!

377
00:28:46,991 --> 00:28:48,617
All right, this is the plan.

378
00:28:48,784 --> 00:28:51,578
I want these guys to sit here,
not on the couch.

379
00:28:53,789 --> 00:28:57,334
Keep the blinds open.
I want the light in their eyes.

380
00:28:57,501 --> 00:29:01,379
I'll sit at the desk. I don't want
you to introduce me. Just start talking.

381
00:29:01,547 --> 00:29:04,424
I want you to stand behind them
as they sit down. Understand?

382
00:29:04,592 --> 00:29:08,178
They'll be looking at you,
but they don't know who you are.

383
00:29:08,346 --> 00:29:12,641
That's right.
Do not tell 'em who I am.

384
00:29:13,726 --> 00:29:16,269
- I gotta say something.
- No, you don't.

385
00:29:18,022 --> 00:29:21,983
Unless it's "Glad you assholes stopped
by, now I can straighten you out."

386
00:29:22,151 --> 00:29:23,610
You're kidding, right?

387
00:29:23,778 --> 00:29:26,655
Just say the movie's been postponed.

388
00:29:26,822 --> 00:29:29,449
And whatever you do,
don't say anything about Mr. Lovejoy.

389
00:29:31,827 --> 00:29:32,953
All right, let's go.

390
00:29:34,830 --> 00:29:36,164
Hey, Ronnie!

391
00:29:36,332 --> 00:29:37,582
Harry, all right!

392
00:29:41,671 --> 00:29:45,048
Have we entered a time warp? I feel
like I'm in Hollywood of yesteryear.

393
00:29:45,216 --> 00:29:47,300
- Have a seat right there.
- Cool.

394
00:29:52,848 --> 00:29:55,892
This is my associate, Chili Palmer.

395
00:29:56,060 --> 00:30:00,355
Just so there's no misunderstanding,

396
00:30:00,523 --> 00:30:04,859
your investment is just as solid
as the day you signed.

397
00:30:05,027 --> 00:30:07,320
I can hear you, man,
but where the fuck are you?

398
00:30:07,488 --> 00:30:08,863
Right here!

399
00:30:10,283 --> 00:30:12,367
What I've been wondering is,
where's he been?

400
00:30:12,535 --> 00:30:16,037
Yeah, where you been, Harry?

401
00:30:16,205 --> 00:30:18,832
New York. I was scouting locations.

402
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:22,794
The main thing is that Freaks will
be put off for a couple of months.

403
00:30:22,962 --> 00:30:24,754
- A couple of months?
- Yeah.

404
00:30:26,590 --> 00:30:31,261
Just a couple of months, yeah.
We need more... prep.

405
00:30:31,429 --> 00:30:34,806
Bullshit, man!
We have an agreement.

406
00:30:34,974 --> 00:30:36,725
We're going to do this picture.

407
00:30:38,394 --> 00:30:42,480
I just have another project first,
one I promised this guy for years.

408
00:30:42,648 --> 00:30:47,569
(Ronnie) I wanna see your books.
Show me a two with five zeros after it.

409
00:30:48,779 --> 00:30:51,781
I wanna see your books,
your fuckin' bank statements...

410
00:30:51,949 --> 00:30:54,075
(Chili) Hey, Ronnie. Look at me.

411
00:30:54,243 --> 00:30:58,830
You have a piece of a movie,
not a piece of Harry.

412
00:30:58,998 --> 00:31:02,459
If he wants to do another movie
this year, that's how it's gonna be.

413
00:31:03,252 --> 00:31:05,253
Excuse me...
but who the fuck are you?

414
00:31:05,421 --> 00:31:07,213
I'm the one telling you how it is.

415
00:31:11,927 --> 00:31:13,845
What is this other movie, Harry?

416
00:31:14,013 --> 00:31:16,598
Harry, let me answer this.

417
00:31:16,766 --> 00:31:19,559
First, who am I talking to, him or you?

418
00:31:19,727 --> 00:31:21,102
You can talk to me.

419
00:31:21,270 --> 00:31:23,855
That's what I thought.
Let me put it this way.

420
00:31:24,023 --> 00:31:27,484
Outside of Freaks, it's none
of your fucking business what we do.

421
00:31:27,651 --> 00:31:29,986
Whoa! Here it is, right here.

422
00:31:30,154 --> 00:31:32,739
This is the project, Mr. Lovejoy.

423
00:31:32,907 --> 00:31:35,784
I'm not puttin' one over on you.

424
00:31:37,661 --> 00:31:39,162
What is it, a porno flick?

425
00:31:39,330 --> 00:31:42,332
It's fluff,
you wouldn't be interested.

426
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:45,502
You think we see your movies?
I've seen better film on teeth.

427
00:31:49,965 --> 00:31:52,717
So how 'bout you just take
our 20 points out of Freaks,

428
00:31:52,885 --> 00:31:55,136
and put it in this other one?

429
00:31:55,304 --> 00:31:57,138
No, I can't do that.

430
00:31:57,306 --> 00:31:58,973
You're positive about that?

431
00:31:59,141 --> 00:32:03,311
Yeah, it's a different kind of deal,
it's structured...

432
00:32:04,814 --> 00:32:07,565
OK. Then be good enough
to hand us our money back.

433
00:32:08,401 --> 00:32:12,028
Or let us come in on this new deal.
Let us know.

434
00:32:12,196 --> 00:32:15,490
By Friday, or you're fuckin'
dead as disco. You hear me?

435
00:32:16,951 --> 00:32:21,079
Take your time, Harry.
We're not animals. Are we, Ronnie?

436
00:32:36,345 --> 00:32:48,690
What?

437
00:32:51,277 --> 00:32:55,113
Maybe I wasn't clear, but I thought
I told you to keep your mouth shut.

438
00:32:55,281 --> 00:32:56,698
I had to tell 'em something.

439
00:32:58,993 --> 00:33:01,244
Never say anything
unless you have to.

440
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:04,038
You asked me to get these guys
off your back.

441
00:33:04,206 --> 00:33:08,710
Then you offer a piece of Mr. Lovejoy.
I couldn't believe my fuckin' ears.

442
00:33:08,878 --> 00:33:12,589
I told them I'd think about it.
In this town, that means nothing.

443
00:33:13,549 --> 00:33:17,051
That's the difference between you
and me, Harry. I say what I mean.

444
00:33:20,014 --> 00:33:24,476
I want Martin Weir, I talk to Martin
Weir, not his trainer's shrink.

445
00:33:24,643 --> 00:33:26,269
Shrink's trainer.

446
00:33:26,437 --> 00:33:27,854
Take me back to my car.

447
00:33:37,531 --> 00:33:39,324
(phone)

448
00:33:40,618 --> 00:33:41,659
Yeah?

449
00:33:41,827 --> 00:33:43,077
Tommo. Chili.

450
00:33:43,245 --> 00:33:46,498
Where you been?
I been lookin' all over.

451
00:33:46,665 --> 00:33:49,959
Ray Bones is looking for you.
Where are you?

452
00:33:50,127 --> 00:33:55,423
I'm in LA now. I'm going into
the movie business. Producing.

453
00:33:55,591 --> 00:33:57,675
What the fuck do you know
about makin' movies?

454
00:33:57,843 --> 00:34:00,470
I don't think the producer
has to know much.

455
00:34:01,388 --> 00:34:03,014
(key in lock)

456
00:34:03,182 --> 00:34:06,100
I gotta go. Call me when
you know more about Bones.

457
00:34:06,268 --> 00:34:09,270
Hey, Karen, how you doin'?

458
00:34:09,438 --> 00:34:10,939
What are you doing here?

459
00:34:11,106 --> 00:34:15,109
Listen, I wanted to apologize
for breaking in last night.

460
00:34:17,279 --> 00:34:20,448
You broke in again to apologize
for breaking in before?

461
00:34:20,616 --> 00:34:24,619
No, your patio door was open.
You shouldn't do that.

462
00:34:24,787 --> 00:34:26,913
Well, lock it on your way out.

463
00:34:27,915 --> 00:34:29,290
You had a bad day, huh?

464
00:34:29,458 --> 00:34:35,129
The director said I couldn't reach
the emotional core of the character.

465
00:34:35,297 --> 00:34:39,467
What? Obviously he didn't see
Bride Of The Mutant.

466
00:34:39,635 --> 00:34:41,511
You saw that one?

467
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:47,308
When you say to the alien mother
that her time on earth is finished,

468
00:34:47,476 --> 00:34:52,355
Joan Crawford, on her best day
wished she had the emotion,

469
00:34:52,523 --> 00:34:53,940
the intensity that you had.

470
00:34:54,984 --> 00:34:57,652
That was a good scene
for a horror movie.

471
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:59,612
No, for any movie.

472
00:34:59,780 --> 00:35:05,326
I know I'm better than walking round
in fuck-me pumps, waiting to scream.

473
00:35:05,494 --> 00:35:06,869
Yeah, but what a scream.

474
00:35:08,872 --> 00:35:13,501
It would be nice to get the chance
to say one great line.

475
00:35:13,669 --> 00:35:17,672
Like when Bette Davis walks up
to the guy

476
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:20,300
and says "I'd kiss you...

477
00:35:20,467 --> 00:35:22,468
...but I just washed my hands".

478
00:35:22,636 --> 00:35:24,721
How come you don't work with Harry?

479
00:35:24,888 --> 00:35:28,683
'Cause I married Martin Weir.
He was a full-time job.

480
00:35:28,851 --> 00:35:31,728
