You leave a trail like a caterpillar.

542
00:39:54,950 --> 00:39:56,242
Hey!

543
00:39:58,245 --> 00:40:01,664
Hey, wait a minute.
What's this 18% shit?

544
00:40:01,832 --> 00:40:05,001
You wanna borrow ten,
the vig is three bills a week.

545
00:40:05,168 --> 00:40:08,337
15 for the vig, plus the ten,
that's 25 big ones.

546
00:40:10,048 --> 00:40:12,341
Hey, you hear... hear me?

547
00:40:47,669 --> 00:40:51,047
This is good. This Mr. Lovejoy...

548
00:40:51,965 --> 00:40:56,093
It needs a better ending, but yes,
I see why Harry wants to do it.

549
00:40:58,764 --> 00:41:01,849
I knew he was lyin',
sayin' this wasn't any good,

550
00:41:02,017 --> 00:41:05,436
but holding on to it,
like you'd have to break his fingers!

551
00:41:06,813 --> 00:41:11,150
That's funny. I was thinking
what I'd have to break of yours.

552
00:41:11,318 --> 00:41:13,569
I'm explaining why I'm here,

553
00:41:13,737 --> 00:41:19,200
in case you thought I came to rob
any of this dusty old shit.

554
00:41:19,368 --> 00:41:21,869
I wouldn't make you out
to be a burglar.

555
00:41:22,037 --> 00:41:25,373
Harry called you his associate.
What does that mean?

556
00:41:25,540 --> 00:41:30,002
I never heard your name,
or read it in Variety or anyplace.

557
00:41:30,170 --> 00:41:32,213
I'm his associate.

558
00:41:32,381 --> 00:41:34,090
You must bring
something heavy to the deal.

559
00:41:34,257 --> 00:41:36,050
I do. Me.

560
00:41:36,843 --> 00:41:39,553
It says here
you're getting Martin Weir.

561
00:41:39,721 --> 00:41:41,389
That's right.

562
00:41:41,556 --> 00:41:43,849
Come on.
How you gonna do that?

563
00:41:44,017 --> 00:41:46,227
I'm gonna take a gun,
put it to his head,

564
00:41:46,395 --> 00:41:49,105
I'm gonna say
"Sign, Martin, or you're dead."

565
00:41:50,899 --> 00:41:53,067
I wonder, would that work?

566
00:41:53,235 --> 00:41:57,571
You know who I see as Al Roxy?
Harvey Keitel.

567
00:41:57,739 --> 00:42:00,157
He was good in that movie Fingers.

568
00:42:01,201 --> 00:42:04,412
You know who else? Morgan Freeman.

569
00:42:04,579 --> 00:42:07,748
Morgan Freeman.
But he's a colored guy.

570
00:42:07,916 --> 00:42:12,253
So what? Where does it say
the man's got to be white?

571
00:42:12,421 --> 00:42:16,424
Color's what the part needs, man.
You need somebody with some style.

572
00:42:17,592 --> 00:42:19,260
So what do you think of the script?

573
00:42:24,433 --> 00:42:27,184
The first thing
that's got to go is the title.

574
00:42:27,352 --> 00:42:30,229
Murray Saffron would be
better than Lovejoy.

575
00:42:30,397 --> 00:42:32,023
I'm with you on that.

576
00:42:34,568 --> 00:42:38,279
Why don't you and I sit down, write
the script over where it needs it.

577
00:42:38,447 --> 00:42:41,240
- You could write one of these?
- Nothin' to it.

578
00:42:41,408 --> 00:42:44,785
You get an idea,
set it down on paper,

579
00:42:44,953 --> 00:42:49,707
then you hire somebody
to fill in the commas and shit,

580
00:42:49,875 --> 00:42:52,668
fix up the spelling,
where you have tricky words.

581
00:42:52,836 --> 00:42:56,130
Although I've seen scripts,
I know words weren't spelt right,

582
00:42:56,298 --> 00:43:00,134
there was hardly any commas at all.
So I don't think that's too important.

583
00:43:00,302 --> 00:43:04,472
You get to the end, fade out.
You done.

584
00:43:04,639 --> 00:43:06,807
That's it?
That's all there is to it?

585
00:43:08,935 --> 00:43:11,145
Then what the fuck
do I need you for?

586
00:43:13,065 --> 00:43:15,900
I'm offering my services, man.

587
00:43:16,068 --> 00:43:20,654
I'll tell you what. If I need
a ride sometime, I'll let you know.

588
00:43:26,036 --> 00:43:28,788
How could you arrest me here?
This is my country.

589
00:43:28,955 --> 00:43:31,665
This is where you're going to die.

590
00:43:35,921 --> 00:43:38,798
That was no miss.

591
00:43:38,965 --> 00:43:41,008
I don't want to shoot you
in the back.

592
00:43:41,176 --> 00:43:43,844
Unless you'd rather
try to run for it.

593
00:43:45,430 --> 00:43:46,972
(gunshot)

594
00:43:50,018 --> 00:43:51,185
Did you bring my wife?

595
00:43:51,353 --> 00:43:53,395
She's in the car.
I've got it all on tape.

596
00:43:53,563 --> 00:43:56,273
- You sure you got enough?
- Go play it back, you'll see.

597
00:43:58,401 --> 00:44:00,653
(indistinct movie dialogue)

598
00:44:04,407 --> 00:44:06,325
That's the second bullet
I stopped for you.

599
00:44:06,493 --> 00:44:09,203
That's the second bullet
I stopped for you.

600
00:44:14,626 --> 00:44:16,752
You're going down, Orson.

601
00:44:21,550 --> 00:44:25,678
lsn't somebody going to come
and take him away?

602
00:44:25,846 --> 00:44:27,429
You really liked him, didn't you?

603
00:44:27,597 --> 00:44:28,848
The cop did.

604
00:44:29,015 --> 00:44:33,227
The cop did. The one who killed him.
He loved him.

605
00:44:33,395 --> 00:44:35,938
Well, Hank was a great detective.

606
00:44:36,106 --> 00:44:38,065
- But a lousy cop.
- But a lousy cop.

607
00:44:39,651 --> 00:44:41,610
ls that all you have to say for him?

608
00:44:42,529 --> 00:44:44,405
He was some kind of a man.

609
00:44:47,993 --> 00:44:50,703
What does it matter
what you say about people?

610
00:44:58,128 --> 00:44:59,545
Goodbye, Karen.

611
00:45:01,256 --> 00:45:04,133
Adios.

612
00:45:12,017 --> 00:45:13,434
Wow, huh?

613
00:45:15,562 --> 00:45:17,146
(sighs)

614
00:45:20,275 --> 00:45:21,650
You've been here the whole time.

615
00:45:21,818 --> 00:45:23,068
No, I just caught the end.

616
00:45:23,236 --> 00:45:28,657
Welles didn't want to do this movie.
He couldn't get out of the contract.

617
00:45:29,826 --> 00:45:33,370
Sometimes you do your best work
when you got a gun to your head.

618
00:45:35,290 --> 00:45:37,041
I brought you a copy of the script.

619
00:45:37,209 --> 00:45:38,918
I've read it.
Harry left a copy at the house.

620
00:45:39,085 --> 00:45:41,212
- How'd you like it?
- It's not horrible.

621
00:45:41,379 --> 00:45:44,131
I don't like the title
or some characters.

622
00:45:44,299 --> 00:45:46,383
- So you read it?
- I haven't yet, but I will.

623
00:45:46,551 --> 00:45:48,510
You and Harry make a great team.

624
00:45:48,678 --> 00:45:50,137
Is that right?

625
00:45:50,305 --> 00:45:53,349
- I'll make a deal with you.
- Oh, found a character you like?

626
00:45:53,516 --> 00:45:56,810
I want to produce it
especially if I help him get Martin.

627
00:45:56,978 --> 00:45:59,480
Hey, that's fair.

628
00:45:59,648 --> 00:46:01,148
So what do you get out of it?

629
00:46:01,316 --> 00:46:03,609
Is that why you came here,
to ask me that?

630
00:46:03,777 --> 00:46:05,319
I wanna know.

631
00:46:05,487 --> 00:46:07,488
Why would anyone
want to be in movies?

632
00:46:07,656 --> 00:46:09,698
Yesterday you were a loan shark.

633
00:46:09,866 --> 00:46:14,245
I was never into it and especially
that bullshit about respect.

634
00:46:14,412 --> 00:46:18,123
It was bad enough
treating these guys like heroes,

635
00:46:18,291 --> 00:46:21,293
those stupid comments
they think are so funny.

636
00:46:21,461 --> 00:46:23,963
You think the movie business
is different?

637
00:46:24,130 --> 00:46:27,258
I like movies and I figured
if I help Harry make one,

638
00:46:27,425 --> 00:46:30,678
I'll find out what to do
outside of having an idea.

639
00:46:33,014 --> 00:46:36,725
I was in the money business
and I have a lot of ideas in my head.

640
00:46:36,893 --> 00:46:39,478
I'm going to talk to Martin tomorrow.

641
00:46:39,646 --> 00:46:43,148
I told Harry I'd meet you and him
at the restaurant afterwards.

642
00:46:46,569 --> 00:46:49,363
This mightjust work out.
You never know.

643
00:46:49,531 --> 00:46:51,532
Sounds fine.

644
00:46:54,744 --> 00:46:56,370
(Chili to himself) Adios.

645
00:47:50,633 --> 00:47:54,845
(Yayo) I spent eight hours at the
airport looking at people's bulges!

646
00:47:55,013 --> 00:47:56,972
This is not the way we do business.

647
00:47:57,140 --> 00:48:01,602
You don't know who you're messing
with. I want the fucking money!

648
00:48:01,770 --> 00:48:06,648
You gonna smoke, you get
the hell off my $70-a-yard carpet.

649
00:48:07,609 --> 00:48:11,612
I told you where the money is.
Now go and get it.

650
00:48:11,780 --> 00:48:17,451
I'll tell you somethin',
if they bust me,

651
00:48:17,619 --> 00:48:20,454
I tell them I come to get something
for you. That's all I know.

652
00:48:20,622 --> 00:48:22,664
- That's all you know, huh?
- That's all I know.

653
00:48:22,832 --> 00:48:25,000
Wait here. I'll be back directly.

654
00:48:27,212 --> 00:48:28,962
Keep an eye on him for me.

655
00:48:40,266 --> 00:48:42,101
That's the way you get things done.

656
00:48:47,732 --> 00:48:49,775
What the fuck
you gonna do with that?

657
00:48:49,943 --> 00:48:51,693
I'm taking you out, yahoo.

658
00:49:03,373 --> 00:49:05,958
See that,
the way the man went right over?

659
00:49:06,126 --> 00:49:08,293
We could get Chili Palmer here.

660
00:49:08,461 --> 00:49:11,839
You could fix my railing
to give way like in the movies.

661
00:49:12,006 --> 00:49:16,343
I invite him to look at my view,
get him to lean over...

662
00:49:16,511 --> 00:49:18,679
It's the dumbest idea I ever heard.

663
00:49:19,889 --> 00:49:21,390
Here's the thing, Bear,

664
00:49:21,558 --> 00:49:26,019
what's the point of living in LA
unless you're in the movie business?

665
00:49:26,187 --> 00:49:31,650
High up in it. That's why Harry's
going to produce Mr. Lovejoywith me,

666
00:49:31,818 --> 00:49:33,694
not Chili Palmer.

667
00:49:55,216 --> 00:49:57,092
I can't believe
this map is accurate.

668
00:49:57,260 --> 00:49:59,636
I bought it from a kid on Sunset.

669
00:49:59,804 --> 00:50:01,889
You were supposed
to meet me at the restaurant.

670
00:50:02,056 --> 00:50:05,225
It says Martin Weir's house
across from George Hamilton.

671
00:50:05,393 --> 00:50:07,102
- That must be...
- Chili?

672
00:50:07,270 --> 00:50:08,812
Nicole?

673
00:50:08,980 --> 00:50:12,441
It's Nicki now.
I don't believe this!

674
00:50:12,609 --> 00:50:13,859
Hey!

675
00:50:14,027 --> 00:50:15,903
- I know her!
- Hi, Nicki.

676
00:50:16,070 --> 00:50:19,198
Karen, shit, I didn't see you.
How are you?

677
00:50:19,365 --> 00:50:21,950
You gotta come in,
you gotta meet Martin!

678
00:50:23,870 --> 00:50:26,497
Where you been?
What have you been doing?

679
00:50:28,249 --> 00:50:31,084
Chili was the only one
who didn't try to hit on me.

680
00:50:31,252 --> 00:50:33,003
What a gentleman.

681
00:50:33,171 --> 00:50:34,755
Do you like my hair black?

682
00:50:34,923 --> 00:50:37,508
Nice, yeah,
especially under the arms.

683
00:50:37,675 --> 00:50:43,305
Martin won't let me shave. Takes
him back to the '60s or something.

684
00:50:45,099 --> 00:50:46,433
Speak of the devil.

685
00:50:46,601 --> 00:50:49,228
Karen, look at you.

686
00:50:49,395 --> 00:50:50,646
Hi, Martin.

687
00:50:52,106 --> 00:50:54,691
You smell so good.
She always smells so good.

688
00:50:54,859 --> 00:50:57,277
Martin, this is Chili Palmer.

689
00:50:57,445 --> 00:50:58,946
Chili, is it?

690
00:50:59,113 --> 00:51:00,614
Nice to meet you, Martin.

691
00:51:00,782 --> 00:51:05,786
Chili ran a club I used to play at
in Miami. How is Momo these days?

692
00:51:05,954 --> 00:51:07,621
Dead.

693
00:51:07,789 --> 00:51:10,457
Bummer. I'll let you
get to your movie talk.

694
00:51:10,625 --> 00:51:13,418
Chili, do not leave
without saying goodbye to me.

695
00:51:17,757 --> 00:51:19,091
So...

696
00:51:21,469 --> 00:51:23,470
You know how beautiful you are?

697
00:51:23,638 --> 00:51:25,264
You really are beautiful.

698
00:51:25,932 --> 00:51:29,518
I'm sitting here looking at you

699
00:51:29,686 --> 00:51:32,271
and having flashbacks, memories of us.

700
00:51:32,438 --> 00:51:34,690
- Really?
- Yeah and I'm wondering...

701
00:51:34,857 --> 00:51:38,443
...how did it all slip away?

702
00:51:38,611 --> 00:51:43,156
It didn't slip away. You did when
you fucked Nicki at my birthday party.

703
00:51:44,701 --> 00:51:46,493
That was a good party.

704
00:51:46,661 --> 00:51:49,079
You know, Marty, you were so good
in that movie, The Cyclone.

705
00:51:49,247 --> 00:51:51,623
Martin. Yeah, it was a beautiful role.

706
00:51:51,791 --> 00:51:54,501
All I had to do
was find the character's center.

707
00:51:54,669 --> 00:51:59,715
The stem I used to wind him up
and he'd just play.

708
00:51:59,882 --> 00:52:04,303
If I didn't know better,
I'd have thought you was a made guy.

709
00:52:04,470 --> 00:52:06,471
No acting there, right?

710
00:52:06,639 --> 00:52:08,640
And the fink part...

711
00:52:08,808 --> 00:52:11,393
I never met a fink
and I hope I never do,

712
00:52:11,561 --> 00:52:14,438
but the way you played a fink,
that's how it's gotta be.

713
00:52:14,606 --> 00:52:15,772
Yeah.

714
00:52:15,940 --> 00:52:18,317
Two weeks before shooting,

715
00:52:18,484 --> 00:52:21,194
I went to Bensonhurst
to hear you guys talk.

716
00:52:21,362 --> 00:52:24,197
I'm Italian, but grew up in Tarzana.

717
00:52:25,533 --> 00:52:27,951
I wanted to get the rhythms
of your speech.

718
00:52:28,995 --> 00:52:30,454
We speak differently?

719
00:52:30,622 --> 00:52:33,040
It was more your attitude, your tone.

