00:52:33,207 --> 00:52:36,877
Your speech patterns demonstrate
confidence in your opinions,

721
00:52:37,045 --> 00:52:39,338
your indifference
to conventional views.

722
00:52:41,007 --> 00:52:42,507
Like we don't give a shit?

723
00:52:42,675 --> 00:52:44,217
Yeah, kinda. Yeah.

724
00:52:45,345 --> 00:52:48,472
Once I get the authentic
sounds of speech,

725
00:52:48,640 --> 00:52:51,558
the patois, you know,

726
00:52:51,726 --> 00:52:56,271
I can actually think the way
those guys do. Get inside.

727
00:52:56,439 --> 00:52:57,898
- Really?
- Yeah.

728
00:52:58,066 --> 00:53:01,026
Well, I'm one of those guys.
What am I thinking?

729
00:53:01,194 --> 00:53:02,986
Well, don't get me wrong,

730
00:53:03,154 --> 00:53:08,075
a metamorphosis doesn't take
place, that wouldn't be acting.

731
00:53:08,242 --> 00:53:11,870
- So you don't know what I'm thinking?
- No, but I have to say I'm curious.

732
00:53:12,038 --> 00:53:14,247
So you want to know?

733
00:53:14,415 --> 00:53:16,875
- If you want to tell me.
- I'm thinking about a movie.

734
00:53:17,043 --> 00:53:18,251
One of mine?

735
00:53:18,419 --> 00:53:20,045
No. One we're producing.

736
00:53:20,213 --> 00:53:22,631
With what? Wise guy money?

737
00:53:25,426 --> 00:53:27,177
Maybe this wasn't a good idea.

738
00:53:27,345 --> 00:53:30,180
I'm not connected to that any more

739
00:53:30,348 --> 00:53:32,724
since I left that
loansharking operation.

740
00:53:32,892 --> 00:53:34,518
The pressure got too much for you?

741
00:53:34,686 --> 00:53:37,104
I'm the one who applied the pressure.

742
00:53:37,271 --> 00:53:40,315
- Oh, yeah?
- Can I ask you a question?

743
00:53:40,483 --> 00:53:42,275
Yeah.

744
00:53:42,443 --> 00:53:45,946
- Actors like to pretend, right?
- We've been known to make believe.

745
00:53:46,114 --> 00:53:50,117
Pretend this. You're a shylock.
A guy owes you 15 grand.

746
00:53:50,284 --> 00:53:53,161
He skips town, he takes off.
What do you do?

747
00:53:59,919 --> 00:54:01,920
(low laugh)

748
00:54:02,088 --> 00:54:03,964
(grunts melodramatically)

749
00:54:06,467 --> 00:54:08,260
Oh, Martin, for Christ's sake...

750
00:54:09,554 --> 00:54:11,638
This is, you know...

751
00:54:12,598 --> 00:54:15,475
I'm doing Shylock
instead of a shylock.

752
00:54:15,643 --> 00:54:17,185
What's my motivation?

753
00:54:17,353 --> 00:54:22,149
The acquisition of money,
to collect, to inflict pain if I must.

754
00:54:22,316 --> 00:54:27,738
Guy splits with my money, I go
after him, what do you think I'd do?

755
00:54:27,905 --> 00:54:30,157
- Look at me.
- I am looking at you.

756
00:54:30,324 --> 00:54:33,910
Look at me the way I'm looking at you.
Put it in your eyes.

757
00:54:34,078 --> 00:54:36,496
"You're mine, asshole,"
without saying it.

758
00:54:37,999 --> 00:54:39,166
OK, how 'bout this?

759
00:54:43,629 --> 00:54:46,673
Are you telling me you're sleepy,
you want to go to bed?

760
00:54:46,841 --> 00:54:49,634
All right, OK.

761
00:54:50,178 --> 00:54:51,887
(strains theatrically)

762
00:54:58,478 --> 00:55:00,854
Now you're squinting
like you need glasses.

763
00:55:02,023 --> 00:55:03,315
What do you...?

764
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:05,525
- Look at me.
- What?

765
00:55:05,693 --> 00:55:09,362
What I'm thinking is
"You're mine. I fuckin' own you."

766
00:55:09,530 --> 00:55:12,324
But I'm not feeling
one way or another about it.

767
00:55:12,492 --> 00:55:17,913
You're not a person to me, you're an
entry in a book, a guy who owes me.

768
00:55:19,248 --> 00:55:21,541
All right, how about this?

769
00:55:25,880 --> 00:55:28,089
Whoa, oh, wow, not bad!

770
00:55:28,257 --> 00:55:30,759
Not bad.
No wonder you're Martin Weir.

771
00:55:33,095 --> 00:55:36,181
That's what I think of you, asshole.
Nothin'.

772
00:55:36,891 --> 00:55:38,892
I believe it.

773
00:55:40,102 --> 00:55:41,978
So I turn this on
when I confront the guy?

774
00:55:42,146 --> 00:55:45,065
You haven't found him yet,
he's split for Las Vegas.

775
00:55:45,233 --> 00:55:47,943
- How do I know that?
- Because his wife told you.

776
00:55:48,110 --> 00:55:50,195
His wife told me. OK.

777
00:55:51,030 --> 00:55:52,447
(convivial laughter)

778
00:55:59,080 --> 00:56:00,580
Harry, how you doing?

779
00:56:00,748 --> 00:56:02,666
Great.

780
00:56:04,293 --> 00:56:06,211
I'm expecting some people.

781
00:56:06,379 --> 00:56:09,965
You must be doing some big deals
doing lunch in a place like this.

782
00:56:10,132 --> 00:56:11,758
I'm working on a few things.

783
00:56:11,926 --> 00:56:14,678
I hear you bagged Martin Weir
for Mr. Lovejoy.

784
00:56:14,846 --> 00:56:17,097
Word gets around, huh?

785
00:56:17,265 --> 00:56:22,519
Chili Palmer told me when
he called me over to talk about it.

786
00:56:22,687 --> 00:56:24,312
He showed you my script?

787
00:56:24,480 --> 00:56:26,898
Yeah. I was wondering
why he would do that.

788
00:56:28,943 --> 00:56:32,612
The wife sues the airline?
Some gutsy babe!

789
00:56:32,780 --> 00:56:34,948
Good looking, too, like Karen.

790
00:56:35,116 --> 00:56:37,701
When do I meet the husband
and give him the look?

791
00:56:37,869 --> 00:56:39,578
That's not so simple.

792
00:56:39,745 --> 00:56:42,289
There's a mob guy.
You owe him money.

793
00:56:42,456 --> 00:56:46,126
He wants to take you out
because you broke his nose.

794
00:56:46,294 --> 00:56:48,378
Keep going.

795
00:56:48,546 --> 00:56:51,798
At this point, basically,
that's gotta be it.

796
00:56:52,550 --> 00:56:54,134
That's all you'll tell me?

797
00:56:54,302 --> 00:56:57,846
The reason we came by
was to talk about Mr. Lovejoy.

798
00:56:58,014 --> 00:57:01,141
We understand that you read
the script and you loved it.

799
00:57:02,393 --> 00:57:03,977
Refresh my memory.

800
00:57:04,145 --> 00:57:07,939
Listen, how'd you like
to get your hands on $500,000?

801
00:57:08,107 --> 00:57:10,817
Pay me back at your convenience,
no interest.

802
00:57:10,985 --> 00:57:12,652
Are you serious?

803
00:57:12,820 --> 00:57:15,113
All I want in return
is to work on this movie with you.

804
00:57:15,281 --> 00:57:19,451
I've got some ideas
on how to fix it up.

805
00:57:19,619 --> 00:57:21,661
(waiter) Can I get you anything else?

806
00:57:21,829 --> 00:57:24,497
Another one for Mr. Zimm. A double.

807
00:57:28,502 --> 00:57:30,962
You're just going to give me
this $500,000?

808
00:57:31,130 --> 00:57:33,673
We'll talk about that
but first I gotta know,

809
00:57:33,841 --> 00:57:36,259
how'd you hook up
with this Chili Palmer?

810
00:57:37,678 --> 00:57:41,514
Mr. Lovejoywas good.
I'll call Buddy, set up a meeting.

811
00:57:41,682 --> 00:57:42,724
Who's Buddy?

812
00:57:42,892 --> 00:57:44,476
- His agent.
- Karen knows him.

813
00:57:44,644 --> 00:57:46,394
- You are interested?
- I'm intrigued.

814
00:57:46,562 --> 00:57:48,772
Take another look at The Cyclone,

815
00:57:48,940 --> 00:57:51,191
the way the visual fabric
is maintained

816
00:57:51,359 --> 00:57:53,652
while the metaphor
plays on different levels.

817
00:57:56,447 --> 00:57:57,739
Is this your ride?

818
00:57:57,907 --> 00:58:00,325
I like to sit high,
check everything out.

819
00:58:00,493 --> 00:58:02,535
It is the Cadillac of mini-vans.

820
00:58:02,703 --> 00:58:04,996
- Ho...
- Check this out.

821
00:58:09,961 --> 00:58:11,670
Mind if I take it for a spin?

822
00:58:15,216 --> 00:58:16,341
(chuckles)

823
00:58:20,471 --> 00:58:22,347
He was watching Letterman, huh?

824
00:58:22,515 --> 00:58:24,224
Sneaky, that Chili Palmer.

825
00:58:24,392 --> 00:58:27,394
Did he ever find that dry-cleaner,
the one with all the money on him?

826
00:58:27,561 --> 00:58:29,729
Leo? I don't know.

827
00:58:30,648 --> 00:58:35,777
I bet he did and he ain't giving you one
penny to help you out, not the way I am.

828
00:58:37,321 --> 00:58:41,157
Assuming I go along with this,
when can I have the $500,000?

829
00:58:41,325 --> 00:58:42,659
Whenever you want.

830
00:58:42,827 --> 00:58:47,831
The money's in $100 bills
in a locker at the airport.

831
00:58:47,999 --> 00:58:49,416
At the airport?

832
00:58:49,583 --> 00:58:51,418
(sniggers)

833
00:58:53,587 --> 00:58:57,132
It was waiting out there on a deal
that didn't go through, Harry.

834
00:58:57,299 --> 00:58:59,009
One you don't want to know about.

835
00:58:59,176 --> 00:59:00,927
I don't know...

836
00:59:01,095 --> 00:59:06,266
It's not a thing you'd do,
so why not send Chili Palmer?

837
00:59:06,434 --> 00:59:10,520
If he gets busted,
you aren't out a thing, Harry.

838
00:59:11,981 --> 00:59:13,273
C18.

839
00:59:13,441 --> 00:59:15,108
The magic number.

840
00:59:16,193 --> 00:59:17,610
Cat.

841
00:59:21,490 --> 00:59:24,242
I'm positive it was Susan Hayward.

842
00:59:24,410 --> 00:59:26,619
It was Rita Hayworth and Glenn Ford.

843
00:59:28,414 --> 00:59:29,873
Excuse me, Harry.

844
00:59:31,292 --> 00:59:32,584
Wait here.

845
00:59:42,428 --> 00:59:44,721
I'd like you to meet
my associate, Bear.

846
00:59:44,889 --> 00:59:48,433
Stuntman, champion weightlifter,
as you might have noticed.

847
00:59:48,601 --> 00:59:50,643
Throws things out I don't want.

848
00:59:51,729 --> 00:59:53,938
Turn around and go back to Miami.

849
00:59:54,106 --> 00:59:56,816
A stunt man. Any good?

850
00:59:57,943 --> 00:59:59,903
Am I any good?

851
01:00:00,071 --> 01:00:01,404
(shouts in pain)

852
01:00:07,203 --> 01:00:08,995
That's not bad for a guy his size.

853
01:00:12,625 --> 01:00:14,918
If you can get out of here
before I take my coat off,

854
01:00:15,086 --> 01:00:18,171
I won't clean up the floor with you.

855
01:00:19,673 --> 01:00:23,426
You don't know me.
You only think you do.

856
01:00:34,980 --> 01:00:39,067
- That guy is a stunt man.
- Yeah, he was in Creatures II.

857
01:00:47,201 --> 01:00:49,202
Rough business, this movie business.

858
01:00:49,370 --> 01:00:51,746
I may go back to loansharking
for a rest!

859
01:00:51,914 --> 01:00:54,374
What are you still doing
with those guys?

860
01:00:54,542 --> 01:00:57,961
He happens to be loaning me
$500,000. No strings.

861
01:00:58,129 --> 01:01:00,171
I can write any kind of agreement.

862
01:01:00,339 --> 01:01:01,881
Cash or check?

863
01:01:02,049 --> 01:01:06,010
Cash. It's in a locker
at the airport at this moment.

864
01:01:06,178 --> 01:01:10,765
A locker at the airport?
Tell me you're not that stupid.

865
01:01:10,933 --> 01:01:14,561
You're being set up.
He's paying you back.

866
01:01:14,728 --> 01:01:16,855
That right? He's setting me up?

867
01:01:17,022 --> 01:01:20,233
Why did Catlett say
I should send you to pick it up,

868
01:01:20,401 --> 01:01:25,155
since you haven't done a thing for
me except show Catlett my script?

869
01:01:26,532 --> 01:01:29,534
You're right,
you're not being set up.

870
01:01:29,702 --> 01:01:31,744
At least Bo has invested
in three of my movies.

871
01:01:31,912 --> 01:01:33,413
We spoke with Martin.

872
01:01:33,581 --> 01:01:34,789
We?

873
01:01:34,957 --> 01:01:36,082
- Chili and me.
- Really?

874
01:01:36,250 --> 01:01:38,418
Told us to call Buddy,
set up a meeting.

875
01:01:38,586 --> 01:01:40,587
A meeting. You and Karen?

876
01:01:40,754 --> 01:01:42,005
Harry...

877
01:01:42,173 --> 01:01:46,426
He's been in town two days
and he thinks he's David O Selznick.

878
01:01:47,761 --> 01:01:52,682
Shall I deal with Bo or will you
talk with your dry-cleaner?

879
01:01:52,850 --> 01:01:55,602
I've found him,
but forget about Leo's money.

880
01:01:55,769 --> 01:01:57,145
Do you have it?

881
01:01:57,313 --> 01:02:01,774
If I gave you Leo's money you'd
have Ray Bones all over your ass.

882
01:02:01,942 --> 01:02:03,276
Who?

883
01:02:03,444 --> 01:02:06,738
Ray Barboni.
He owns Leo now that Momo's dead.

884
01:02:06,906 --> 01:02:09,991
Who the fuck is Momo?
Where do you get these names?

885
01:02:10,159 --> 01:02:14,287
I'll go to the airport

886
01:02:14,455 --> 01:02:16,706
and if there's no
problem I'll get your money.

887
01:02:16,874 --> 01:02:19,000
I wouldn't get my hopes up.

888
01:02:19,168 --> 01:02:22,962
Maybe I'll call Barboni and ask him
if he wants to invest in my movie.

889
01:02:23,130 --> 01:02:27,467
He's not a movie fan. Gimme the key.

890
01:02:28,552 --> 01:02:30,970
(Karen) Oh, Harry.

891
01:02:34,725 --> 01:02:36,935
Tell him he's got to be out by 5:00am.

892
01:02:37,102 --> 01:02:38,603
(knock on door)

893
01:02:38,771 --> 01:02:40,980
The actor'll only work one night.

894
01:02:41,857 --> 01:02:43,733
I gotta go. Yeah.

895
01:02:47,321 --> 01:02:48,738
Coming!

896
01:02:51,242 --> 01:02:53,159
- Who is it?
- Me.

897
01:02:53,327 --> 01:02:54,535
Oh, fuck!

898
01:02:55,287 --> 01:02:56,663
I heard that.

899
01:02:57,456 --> 01:02:59,040
Hello, Doris!

900
01:02:59,208 --> 01:03:02,543
Harry Zimm!
You look like a wet kiss.

901
01:03:02,711 --> 01:03:04,879
Mmm!

902
01:03:05,047 --> 01:03:09,259
Yum! Aren't you gonna offer me
whatever it is you taste like?

903
01:03:10,886 --> 01:03:11,970
Come in, Doris.

904
01:03:12,137 --> 01:03:15,056
My favorite color! Putty.

905
01:03:15,849 --> 01:03:17,684
(chuckles) Yeah, I like it.

906
01:03:18,644 --> 01:03:20,186
What do you want, Doris?

907
01:03:29,196 --> 01:03:31,364
I miss Murray, Harry.

908
01:03:31,532 --> 01:03:34,867
Yeah, I miss him, too.
Hell of a good writer.

909
01:03:37,288 --> 01:03:38,705
I made him what he was.

910
01:03:38,872 --> 01:03:43,209
He was a hack. He couldn't get a job
writing for anybody but you.

911
01:03:44,837 --> 01:03:48,381
I'm being honest. He was
a lousy writer but a good husband.

912
01:03:48,549 --> 01:03:50,800
I didn't know till it was too late.

913
01:03:50,968 --> 01:03:54,095
Yeah, well, 20/20 hindsight
and all that.

914
01:03:55,264 --> 01:04:00,268
I hate being alone.
The house is so quiet, so lonely.

915
01:04:02,229 --> 01:04:03,771
It needs...

916
01:04:04,690 --> 01:04:06,149
...a man's touch.

917
01:04:07,818 --> 01:04:09,944
Nice necklace, Doris.

918
01:04:13,032 --> 01:04:15,241
Mmm!

919
01:04:16,368 --> 01:04:17,702
Doris...

920
01:04:18,871 --> 01:04:20,830
I don't know how I feel about this.

921
01:04:21,749 --> 01:04:23,583
You seem to feel fine about it.

922
01:04:25,169 --> 01:04:28,129
I mean morally. Murray was a friend.

923
01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:29,589
Murray's dead.

924
01:04:33,510 --> 01:04:37,930
Does this mean you'll reconsider
our deal on Mr. Lovejoy?

925
01:04:38,098 --> 01:04:42,935
No, but I talked to a gorgeous
young executive at Paramount

926
01:04:43,103 --> 01:04:45,855
who happened
to get his hands on the script.

927
01:04:46,023 --> 01:04:47,023
What'd he say?

928
01:04:47,191 --> 01:04:50,276
He said if Martin's interested,
I can get half a million for it.

929
01:04:52,279 --> 01:04:56,366
Don't worry, Harry.
I'm still gonna give you till Friday.

930
01:04:57,117 --> 01:04:58,493
How honorable of you.

931
01:04:58,660 --> 01:05:01,579
Harry, you want me to go,

932
01:05:01,747 --> 01:05:03,498
just say so.

933
01:05:06,460 --> 01:05:08,753
(sighs) Oh, what the hell?

934
01:05:16,053 --> 01:05:17,553
(phone)

935
01:05:17,721 --> 01:05:18,971
Fuck.

936
01:05:21,558 --> 01:05:25,645
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

937
01:05:30,317 --> 01:05:31,317
What?

938
01:05:31,485 --> 01:05:32,693
Ray Barboni?

939
01:05:32,861 --> 01:05:34,070
Who is this?

940
01:05:34,238 --> 01:05:35,988
ls this Ray Bones?

941
01:05:36,156 --> 01:05:38,241
It depends. Who is this?

942
01:05:39,743 --> 01:05:43,913
This is the one telling you
the way it is. OK, asshole?

943
01:05:44,081 --> 01:05:46,499
You want your 300 grand or not?

944
01:05:46,667 --> 01:05:48,584
What 300 grand?

945
01:05:48,752 --> 01:05:52,255
The 300 grand Leo Devoe
scammed off an airline.

946
01:05:52,423 --> 01:05:56,551
The 300 grand that Chili Palmer
now has in his possession.

947
01:05:59,138 --> 01:06:01,347
Hello? Are you there?

948
01:06:01,515 --> 01:06:06,352
I don't like this anonymous crap.
You're either a big chickenshit,

949
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:07,979
or you're not for real.

950
01:06:08,147 --> 01:06:10,022
I am very for real.

951
01:06:10,190 --> 01:06:11,524
So who are you?

952
01:06:11,692 --> 01:06:14,360
I work for Harry Zimm.

953
01:06:14,528 --> 01:06:15,528
Who?

954
01:06:15,696 --> 01:06:19,198
Harry Zimm,
a major Hollywood player.

955
01:06:19,366 --> 01:06:20,658
I never heard of him.

956
01:06:20,826 --> 01:06:23,828
Because you've never left
fucking Miami, dipshit.

957
01:06:23,996 --> 01:06:28,207
Maybe you ought to come out to LA
and meet Mr. Zimm.

958
01:06:29,293 --> 01:06:32,712
OK, so this Zimm guy
is asking for a finder's fee?

959
01:06:34,548 --> 01:06:39,927
Zimm don't ask for dick.
Zimm tells you the way it is, or else.

960
01:06:42,222 --> 01:06:43,431
Or else what?

961
01:06:43,599 --> 01:06:45,558
Use your fucking imagination!

962
01:06:46,101 --> 01:06:47,393
(hangs up)

963
01:08:05,973 --> 01:08:07,974
Excuse me, could you help me out?

964
01:08:08,141 --> 01:08:13,437
I got a surprise gift in here for my
wife. Could you put it in locker C17?

965
01:08:14,773 --> 01:08:17,358
Ten bucks. Take you two minutes.

966
