I don't work for you no more.

1209
01:23:52,168 --> 01:23:55,045
I came down
to tell you to your face.

1210
01:23:55,213 --> 01:23:58,048
The Colombians are in LA,
upset about their money,

1211
01:23:58,216 --> 01:24:02,427
and it turns out Yayo
was Escobar's nephew.

1212
01:24:02,595 --> 01:24:04,930
That's your problem.
You shot the guy.

1213
01:24:07,934 --> 01:24:12,395
Farrah! Hey, honey bunny!
Come here, honey bunny!

1214
01:24:12,563 --> 01:24:17,484
Come and see Uncle Bo, come on.
Uncle Bo hates being alone.

1215
01:24:19,237 --> 01:24:23,532
He hates it so much, if he takes a fall,
he's not gonna fall by himself.

1216
01:24:23,699 --> 01:24:25,909
He's gonna plea-deal his way out.

1217
01:24:26,077 --> 01:24:29,287
Give up his ace stunt man, now one
of the West Coast's dope kings,

1218
01:24:29,455 --> 01:24:31,039
if they go easy on him.

1219
01:24:31,999 --> 01:24:36,753
In Federal joints, you get extra time
with your daddy on Father's Day.

1220
01:24:37,463 --> 01:24:39,422
Let her go, Bo.

1221
01:24:46,138 --> 01:24:50,100
After this one, I'm out.
It's the last time we talk.

1222
01:24:50,268 --> 01:24:53,979
Remember Harry's story about
the dry-cleaner Palmer was after,

1223
01:24:54,146 --> 01:24:58,483
- who stole 300 grand from the airline?
- What about him?

1224
01:24:58,651 --> 01:25:02,821
You go look around Palmer's hotel room
while I check out Karen Flores's place.

1225
01:25:04,699 --> 01:25:06,575
Meet me back here at midnight.

1226
01:25:11,289 --> 01:25:13,748
What kind of food is it at the Ivy?

1227
01:25:13,916 --> 01:25:16,835
Continental, but Martin
won't order from the menu.

1228
01:25:17,003 --> 01:25:18,044
Why not?

1229
01:25:18,212 --> 01:25:23,049
Movie stars have to think of
something that isn't on the menu.

1230
01:25:31,350 --> 01:25:34,185
Harry, you should be
in the hospital!

1231
01:25:34,353 --> 01:25:37,564
You look like you're in
one of your own horror movies.

1232
01:25:37,732 --> 01:25:39,691
(muffled)

1233
01:25:39,859 --> 01:25:42,027
- What'd he say?
- "My project."

1234
01:25:42,194 --> 01:25:43,862
Mr. Zimm!

1235
01:25:45,197 --> 01:25:48,033
Hey, Harry! Attaboy, killer!

1236
01:25:49,035 --> 01:25:50,535
Right this way.

1237
01:25:55,958 --> 01:25:59,794
You're a celebrity. You shoulda
shot someone a long time ago.

1238
01:25:59,962 --> 01:26:01,755
(muffled chuckle)

1239
01:26:08,304 --> 01:26:13,725
Hi.

1240
01:26:13,893 --> 01:26:17,812
'Scuse me. How you doin'?
Hello. Hi.

1241
01:26:18,939 --> 01:26:21,191
How you doin'? Hey, Chili.

1242
01:26:21,359 --> 01:26:23,276
Good to see you.

1243
01:26:24,820 --> 01:26:27,822
Harry! Oh, my goodness!

1244
01:26:33,663 --> 01:26:36,164
- Hi, Martin.
- Sweet face.

1245
01:26:36,332 --> 01:26:38,416
You look great. You smell good, too.

1246
01:26:38,584 --> 01:26:39,793
Thanks.

1247
01:26:43,547 --> 01:26:47,133
So, Harry, I hear you had
quite an experience.

1248
01:26:47,301 --> 01:26:49,928
Anyway, I'm glad you're OK.

1249
01:26:51,555 --> 01:26:56,184
I'm glad you rejected me ten years ago
for the part of Eddie Solomon,

1250
01:26:56,352 --> 01:26:58,395
the pedophile clown.

1251
01:26:58,562 --> 01:27:01,773
If I'd have gotten that part,
I might have been typecast!

1252
01:27:02,983 --> 01:27:05,944
Have you guys ordered?
Can we order?

1253
01:27:06,112 --> 01:27:08,196
Excuse me, could you...?

1254
01:27:08,948 --> 01:27:10,365
- Hi, what's your name?
- Stephanie.

1255
01:27:10,533 --> 01:27:12,242
Hi, Stephanie.

1256
01:27:12,410 --> 01:27:14,160
Can you make an egg white omelet

1257
01:27:14,328 --> 01:27:19,124
with slightly brown shallots
and no salt?

1258
01:27:19,291 --> 01:27:22,001
Bring one for the table.

1259
01:27:22,169 --> 01:27:23,461
No...

1260
01:27:23,629 --> 01:27:28,883
How about those strawberry frappes,
drinks with little strawberries?

1261
01:27:29,051 --> 01:27:31,553
And bring two straws for Harry.

1262
01:27:32,888 --> 01:27:37,100
