your organization is.

1313
01:31:06,143 --> 01:31:09,854
How about I count to three and organize
your brain all over the wall back there?

1314
01:31:10,022 --> 01:31:11,272
How 'bout that? One...

1315
01:31:11,440 --> 01:31:12,982
You're gonna shoot me now, huh?

1316
01:31:13,150 --> 01:31:15,860
- Just a second. Two...
- (laughing) I can't believe this...

1317
01:31:16,028 --> 01:31:18,488
- (screams)
- (gunshots)

1318
01:31:21,659 --> 01:31:22,867
Karen!

1319
01:31:23,035 --> 01:31:24,869
She can't talk right now.

1320
01:31:26,538 --> 01:31:29,040
Nice scream.
They oughta give you more work.

1321
01:31:29,208 --> 01:31:32,251
I'll get you the money,
but it's not here.

1322
01:31:32,419 --> 01:31:35,380
Fine. In the meantime,
I'll hold onto her.

1323
01:31:38,133 --> 01:31:41,427
I'm at 8150 Wonderland Avenue,
right off Laurel Canyon.

1324
01:31:41,595 --> 01:31:43,388
- I'll be there, Karen.
- (muffled cries)

1325
01:31:54,066 --> 01:31:56,859
- You get the money?
- No. What is this?

1326
01:31:57,027 --> 01:31:58,528
Plan B.

1327
01:32:00,572 --> 01:32:02,490
You make yourself comfortable.

1328
01:32:04,034 --> 01:32:07,328
(raised voices)

1329
01:32:09,456 --> 01:32:11,207
Oh, for Christ's sake!

1330
01:32:15,004 --> 01:32:16,129
Calm down, Bear.

1331
01:32:16,296 --> 01:32:19,424
- This is life in prison!
- Don't fade on me now, Bear.

1332
01:32:19,591 --> 01:32:23,845
You gonna shoot me now?
Put me out of my misery!

1333
01:32:24,013 --> 01:32:28,558
Calm down, unless you wanna spend
your life with Farrah on your lap

1334
01:32:28,726 --> 01:32:30,476
in a roomful of felons!

1335
01:32:30,644 --> 01:32:32,270
(door closes)

1336
01:32:32,438 --> 01:32:37,108
So! This is one of them houses
that hang off the side of the cliff.

1337
01:32:38,068 --> 01:32:39,110
Where's Karen?

1338
01:32:39,278 --> 01:32:42,321
In my bathroom. Where's the money?

1339
01:32:47,661 --> 01:32:49,912
- Let me see her.
- Go ahead.

1340
01:32:50,831 --> 01:32:53,958
Karen! Are you OK?

1341
01:32:54,126 --> 01:32:56,461
Guy's got a fucking pink toilet.

1342
01:32:56,628 --> 01:32:59,839
She's great! Give me the money.

1343
01:33:00,007 --> 01:33:02,717
I'm gonna settle something.

1344
01:33:02,885 --> 01:33:06,637
I've been shot up before, three times,

1345
01:33:06,805 --> 01:33:07,889
and I'm still here.

1346
01:33:08,057 --> 01:33:10,099
I'm gonna be here as long as I want.

1347
01:33:10,267 --> 01:33:14,312
So you gotta be nowhere near me,
Karen or Harry.

1348
01:33:14,480 --> 01:33:16,731
Take your money,

1349
01:33:16,899 --> 01:33:20,818
and leave the movie business to those
of us who know what we're doing.

1350
01:33:21,653 --> 01:33:23,112
Come on, Karen.

1351
01:33:28,786 --> 01:33:31,245
You broke in my house
and I have a witness.

1352
01:33:31,413 --> 01:33:32,413
What?

1353
01:33:32,581 --> 01:33:36,084
And it ain't John Wayne
or Dean Martin in El Dorado.

1354
01:33:36,251 --> 01:33:40,588
That was Rio Bravo.
Robert Mitchum was in El Dorado.

1355
01:33:40,756 --> 01:33:44,634
Dean Martin was in Rio Bravo.
Basically the same part.

1356
01:33:44,802 --> 01:33:48,346
John Wayne played John Wayne in both.

1357
01:33:48,514 --> 01:33:50,473
I can't wait for you to be dead.

1358
01:33:50,641 --> 01:33:52,225
Are you gonna let him...?

1359
01:33:55,604 --> 01:33:58,356
That's for the stairs,
and that's for the airport!

1360
01:33:58,524 --> 01:34:01,192
Get him off my carpet
before he starts to bleed.

1361
01:34:06,240 --> 01:34:10,827
Make it look like he came at us,
you shoot him. Self-defense.

1362
01:34:10,994 --> 01:34:13,788
Shouldn't he have a weapon,
a knife or something?

1363
01:34:13,956 --> 01:34:15,039
I'll get it later.

1364
01:34:15,207 --> 01:34:17,375
Bear, that's enough.

1365
01:34:17,543 --> 01:34:22,421
He's gonna look like somebody
beat him up and then shot him.

1366
01:34:23,549 --> 01:34:24,924
No, he ain't.

1367
01:34:30,848 --> 01:34:33,015
(both) Waah!!

1368
01:34:33,725 --> 01:34:35,518
(Bear) Hold on, man!

1369
01:34:35,686 --> 01:34:38,062
- Chili!
- What the hell are you doin'?

1370
01:34:38,230 --> 01:34:40,106
(Chili) Karen,
what the fuck are you doing?

1371
01:34:40,274 --> 01:34:42,233
She's shooting at us! Come on!

1372
01:34:47,322 --> 01:34:50,533
Oh! I'm sorry! I'm sorry.

1373
01:34:52,286 --> 01:34:53,744
Wow.

1374
01:34:56,498 --> 01:34:58,374
How do you think that happened?

1375
01:34:58,542 --> 01:35:00,626
Beats the shit outta me.

1376
01:35:14,141 --> 01:35:15,683
Were you scared up there?

1377
01:35:15,851 --> 01:35:17,018
You bet.

1378
01:35:17,186 --> 01:35:18,603
You don't act like it.

1379
01:35:18,770 --> 01:35:22,190
I was scared then, not now.
How long you want me to be scared?

1380
01:35:24,067 --> 01:35:25,318
I'll be right back.

1381
01:35:46,965 --> 01:35:48,341
How'd you get in here?

1382
01:35:48,508 --> 01:35:52,261
I told them I was you. I acted
real stupid and they believed me.

1383
01:35:53,180 --> 01:35:54,889
What brings you to LA, Bones?

1384
01:35:55,057 --> 01:35:58,517
Don't insult me, just turn around!

1385
01:36:00,812 --> 01:36:05,274
You're the dumbest fuck I ever met.
Lemme take a look in these pockets.

1386
01:36:05,442 --> 01:36:08,694
You shoulda told me about Leo Devoe.

1387
01:36:08,862 --> 01:36:10,112
Why would I do that?

1388
01:36:10,280 --> 01:36:12,865
Because the guy is
a customer of mine, dummy!

1389
01:36:15,661 --> 01:36:18,955
Well, well, well!
What have we here?

1390
01:36:20,123 --> 01:36:22,250
C18.

1391
01:36:22,417 --> 01:36:25,711
I wonder what this could be!
A locker key?

1392
01:36:26,338 --> 01:36:27,838
But where's the locker?

1393
01:36:28,006 --> 01:36:30,091
I checked the bag at the airport.

1394
01:36:31,009 --> 01:36:34,679
Which terminal?

1395
01:36:34,846 --> 01:36:36,180
Sovereign.

1396
01:36:39,643 --> 01:36:41,644
You found Leo, huh?

1397
01:36:41,812 --> 01:36:45,898
You found him, you took his money,
you put it in a locker ready to go?

1398
01:36:47,317 --> 01:36:48,985
Why haven't you left?

1399
01:36:49,152 --> 01:36:50,903
I like it out here.

1400
01:36:53,907 --> 01:36:58,869
I been thinking, there's no reason
why you and I shouldn't get along.

1401
01:36:59,788 --> 01:37:01,872
Forget about that stuff.

1402
01:37:02,040 --> 01:37:04,542
I don't even remember
how all this started.

1403
01:37:04,710 --> 01:37:08,045
You took a swing at me. Fuck it.

1404
01:37:08,213 --> 01:37:10,548
You owe me money. Fuck that.

1405
01:37:10,716 --> 01:37:13,801
You owe me the juice on the money.
Fuck that too.

1406
01:37:13,969 --> 01:37:15,928
I say live and let die.

1407
01:37:16,096 --> 01:37:20,766
But this is strictly between you and I.

1408
01:37:22,185 --> 01:37:25,313
You say nothing to nobody about this.
Understood?

1409
01:37:25,480 --> 01:37:26,814
Whatever you say, Ray.

1410
01:37:26,982 --> 01:37:28,899
I think it's only fair. Don't you?

1411
01:37:30,319 --> 01:37:33,237
Then it's all settled.
I'll see you around.

1412
01:37:36,533 --> 01:37:37,908
Dumb fuck.

1413
01:37:38,076 --> 01:37:46,042
(chuckles)

1414
01:37:53,383 --> 01:37:54,592
Come here.

1415
01:38:02,392 --> 01:38:03,392
The fucking airport.

1416
01:38:03,560 --> 01:38:04,560
(plane overhead)

1417
01:38:53,276 --> 01:38:54,819
Bingo, boys, let's go.

1418
01:38:55,654 --> 01:38:57,822
Hey, Bones! Look at me.

1419
01:39:03,078 --> 01:39:05,413
Fuck you, fuckball!

1420
01:39:06,415 --> 01:39:07,832
Aaagh!!

1421
01:39:08,708 --> 01:39:09,959
Damn!

1422
01:39:10,127 --> 01:39:12,253
Cut! Cut!

1423
01:39:12,421 --> 01:39:14,547
I am pushing the right button.

1424
01:39:14,714 --> 01:39:18,050
- You're not!
- I'm pushing the right button.

1425
01:39:18,885 --> 01:39:21,429
Bear, show him how to do it, OK?

1426
01:39:22,514 --> 01:39:24,390
What do you wanna do, Harry?

1427
01:39:25,475 --> 01:39:30,146
Wrap. It's a wrap.
Come back tomorrow. Fuck!

1428
01:39:30,313 --> 01:39:33,607
You should've gone into overtime
to get that shot.

1429
01:39:33,775 --> 01:39:36,527
It's the second day
and we're two weeks behind.

1430
01:39:37,904 --> 01:39:40,698
And do me a favor, Harry. Next time...

1431
01:39:40,866 --> 01:39:43,659
Martin already told me that he loves it.

1432
01:39:43,827 --> 01:39:46,370
Look, Buddy.
I don't think Martin is right.

1433
01:39:46,538 --> 01:39:49,540
- Why the hell not?!
- Because he's too short. Come on.

1434
01:39:50,709 --> 01:39:52,626
Why does he keep pushing Martin?

1435
01:39:52,794 --> 01:39:54,003
Packaging.

1436
01:39:54,171 --> 01:39:56,922
You can't make a Martin Weir
into a Mel Gibson.

1437
01:39:57,090 --> 01:40:01,010
Where do you wanna go?
Do you wanna go downtown?

